00:52:45.828 --> 00:52:47.705
I'm not gonna change my mind.

499
00:52:47.872 --> 00:52:51.834
Get out of here, before I decide
to come with you, huh? Ha, ha.

500
00:52:52.001 --> 00:52:54.462
Bye, Fif. Thanks.

501
00:52:58.132 --> 00:53:00.384
You'll be back, Rockatansky!

502
00:53:01.761 --> 00:53:03.012
You're hooked, Max,

503
00:53:03.596 --> 00:53:04.639
and you know it!

504
00:54:10.788 --> 00:54:15.376
I've never been able to say things to you,
Jess. About how I feel.

505
00:54:17.795 --> 00:54:20.381
Guess I always counted
on you understanding.

506
00:54:28.139 --> 00:54:29.974
When I was a kid

507
00:54:30.516 --> 00:54:33.853
me and my father used to go
for long walks.

508
00:54:37.148 --> 00:54:39.400
I remember staring down at his shoes.

509
00:54:41.068 --> 00:54:44.238
They were special shoes. Brown.

510
00:54:45.198 --> 00:54:48.075
And he always kept them real shiny.

511
00:54:50.203 --> 00:54:54.665
He was tall,
and he used to take long strides.

512
00:54:55.791 --> 00:54:58.419
And there I'd be right alongside him

513
00:54:58.794 --> 00:55:00.922
just trying to keep up with him.

514
00:55:04.800 --> 00:55:09.347
I don't think he ever knew
how proud I felt of him.

515
00:55:11.599 --> 00:55:14.602
Or how good it felt
just to be there alongside him.

516
00:55:17.563 --> 00:55:20.608
Even now, when I think back on it,
I still feel...

517
00:55:25.029 --> 00:55:27.114
The thing is, Jess

518
00:55:28.616 --> 00:55:32.453
I couldn't tell him about it then,
but I can tell you about it now.

519
00:55:36.207 --> 00:55:40.461
I don't wanna wait 10 years to tell you
how I'm feeling about you right now.

520
00:56:06.696 --> 00:56:07.780
Hello?

521
00:56:08.239 --> 00:56:10.950
- Get a load of that!
- We had a blowout a while back.

522
00:56:11.117 --> 00:56:14.537
Raunchy, very raunchy.
Is the motor okay?

523
00:56:14.704 --> 00:56:17.206
Yeah, the motor's fine.
Look, about this tire...

524
00:56:17.373 --> 00:56:20.873
Don't do much work on these myself,
except to scrape them off the road.

525
00:56:21.002 --> 00:56:24.252
- Yeah. Hey, how about this tire, huh?
- Have it fixed in no time.

526
00:56:24.380 --> 00:56:26.840
I can sell you a set of Dunlops
for next to nothing.

527
00:56:26.924 --> 00:56:29.343
- No, thanks.
- I can't remember where I got them,

528
00:56:29.427 --> 00:56:31.136
but I got them, know what I mean?

529
00:56:31.220 --> 00:56:34.557
No, we'll be all right
just as soon as we get this fixed.

530
00:56:34.765 --> 00:56:36.267
- Max?
- Yeah?

531
00:56:37.852 --> 00:56:38.936
Listen

532
00:56:39.812 --> 00:56:42.773
Sproggo's talked me
into buying him an ice cream, so

533
00:56:43.441 --> 00:56:45.109
I think I'll see you later.

534
00:56:45.276 --> 00:56:47.903
Sure, there's a shop just down the beach.

535
00:56:48.404 --> 00:56:49.947
They'll appreciate the business.

536
00:56:50.031 --> 00:56:52.033
Sure, thanks.

537
00:56:52.491 --> 00:56:54.327
Toodle pip.

538
00:56:56.746 --> 00:56:58.039
Bye.

539
00:57:07.757 --> 00:57:11.052
You just trucking around?
Good time for just trucking.

540
00:57:11.635 --> 00:57:14.597
Wish I could do a bit myself.
Which way you heading? North?

541
00:57:14.764 --> 00:57:16.265
Uh, maybe.

542
00:57:46.337 --> 00:57:48.672
Look what's turned up for Sunday dinner.

543
00:57:49.715 --> 00:57:52.426
Main course and dessert.

544
00:57:53.010 --> 00:57:54.929
My favorite kind

545
00:57:55.596 --> 00:57:57.181
female.

546
00:58:32.967 --> 00:58:34.760
Mm.

547
00:58:37.555 --> 00:58:41.809
Watch the tongue, sweetheart.
I've seen him lick his eyebrow clean.

548
00:59:13.257 --> 00:59:15.092
You must've spent some loot.

549
00:59:15.384 --> 00:59:18.846
Like the sign says,
speed's just a question of money.

550
00:59:19.013 --> 00:59:20.973
How fast do you wanna go?

551
00:59:21.140 --> 00:59:22.940
- Max, quick, get in.
- What's wrong?

552
00:59:23.058 --> 00:59:24.810
Just take my word for it, get in!

553
00:59:24.977 --> 00:59:27.563
- What about the tire?
- Please, Max!

554
00:59:30.107 --> 00:59:31.650
Your tire, man!

555
00:59:32.443 --> 00:59:33.861
Hey, fella!

556
00:59:34.069 --> 00:59:35.738
Watch your tire!

557
00:59:39.116 --> 00:59:40.701
Crazy people!

558
00:59:41.118 --> 00:59:43.329
The world's full of crazy people.

559
01:00:00.971 --> 01:00:02.848
That wagon, was it here?

560
01:00:03.015 --> 01:00:04.266
Sure, a couple with a kid.

561
01:00:04.350 --> 01:00:06.017
- Who are they?
- I was just fixing their tire.

562
01:00:06.101 --> 01:00:10.564
They left their goddamn spare.
Not a bad one either. Ha, ha.

563
01:00:10.773 --> 01:00:12.858
- Who are they?
- A couple

564
01:00:13.400 --> 01:00:16.862
passing through.
Said they were heading north. Maybe.

565
01:00:29.833 --> 01:00:31.585
You want to drive the car? No?

566
01:00:31.752 --> 01:00:34.922
You'd rather play with the ball?
Into the back.

567
01:00:35.089 --> 01:00:36.465
There you go.

568
01:00:38.008 --> 01:00:41.804
I can still see his face now.
Looked as if he'd just swallowed a brick.

569
01:00:41.971 --> 01:00:44.848
What a mean old lady you are.
Huh, Sproggy?

570
01:00:45.015 --> 01:00:47.351
- That's enough from you, mate!
- The dog.

571
01:00:53.023 --> 01:00:55.025
What's the matter with you?

572
01:00:58.779 --> 01:01:00.698
What you got there, pal?

573
01:01:04.076 --> 01:01:05.494
Max!

574
01:01:10.457 --> 01:01:13.252
Yeah, yeah, that's the way I see it too.

575
01:01:13.544 --> 01:01:16.547
Yep. Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

576
01:01:16.714 --> 01:01:19.967
Sure. It's been nice talking to you. Bye.

577
01:01:21.468 --> 01:01:22.886
Take it you agreed with him.

578
01:01:23.053 --> 01:01:25.653
- If they're not worried, I'm not.
- What about that?

579
01:01:27.850 --> 01:01:29.435
I figure it's lost property.

580
01:01:29.602 --> 01:01:32.896
If no one makes a claim to it,
I say we can forget it.

581
01:01:34.857 --> 01:01:36.859
Sounds okay to me, Jess.

582
01:01:37.026 --> 01:01:38.444
Don't know.

583
01:01:38.611 --> 01:01:42.072
If Ziggy says so, believe me, it's okay.

584
01:01:42.406 --> 01:01:45.034
Now, May's expecting you up at the farm.

585
01:01:45.200 --> 01:01:49.663
You'll have no more trouble up there.
Just green grass and fat cows.

586
01:02:22.112 --> 01:02:25.366
- How are you doing?
- Mm. I'm getting there.

587
01:02:32.539 --> 01:02:36.710
I reckon you ought to connect
the doohickey to the gizmo.

588
01:02:39.880 --> 01:02:41.215
Come here, you.

589
01:02:41.382 --> 01:02:44.301
You touch me with those hands
and I'll rip you apart. No!

590
01:02:44.468 --> 01:02:46.220
No, look at them!

591
01:02:46.387 --> 01:02:48.889
- No! No!
- You gonna give me a hug?

592
01:02:49.056 --> 01:02:50.099
No, no...

593
01:03:05.823 --> 01:03:08.325
May told me about the little beach
down by the trees.

594
01:03:08.409 --> 01:03:10.035
- Mm.
- Do you want to come?

595
01:03:10.911 --> 01:03:12.204
Love to

596
01:03:12.371 --> 01:03:16.458
except that I've gotta fix the fan belt,
or we're never gonna get out of here.

597
01:03:16.625 --> 01:03:19.253
Okay, Tarzan,
I'll bring you back some bananas.

598
01:03:19.420 --> 01:03:20.754
All right.

599
01:03:32.683 --> 01:03:34.143
Hey!

600
01:03:54.371 --> 01:03:58.459
Jessie. If you meet Benno down there,
don't let him bother you.

601
01:03:58.625 --> 01:04:00.627
He's only a baby.

602
01:04:02.379 --> 01:04:04.047
Sure, May.

603
01:04:38.916 --> 01:04:40.000
Here, boy.

604
01:07:50.524 --> 01:07:52.526
Jessie, Jessie, wait a minute.

605
01:07:52.734 --> 01:07:55.696
Calm down, now,
and tell me what's the matter.

606
01:07:55.904 --> 01:07:57.823
Very, very naughty.

607
01:07:57.990 --> 01:08:00.575
- Now you tell May what you...
- May.

608
01:08:00.784 --> 01:08:04.496
May, you go and call Ziggy.
Call Ziggy,

609
01:08:04.663 --> 01:08:07.124
and tell him to get here
as fast as he can.

610
01:08:07.290 --> 01:08:08.875
Why, what's going on?

611
01:08:09.042 --> 01:08:12.713
I think we've got some biker trouble.
It's gonna be all right.

612
01:08:12.879 --> 01:08:17.217
Come on, darling. Come on, Jessie.
Well, let's go into the house.

613
01:08:18.552 --> 01:08:21.513
It's gonna be all right.
It's gonna be all right.

614
01:08:30.731 --> 01:08:34.067
You've had an awful time, darling,

615
01:08:34.818 --> 01:08:37.571
but it's all over now.

616
01:08:37.946 --> 01:08:40.907
Everything's going to be all right.

617
01:08:45.370 --> 01:08:47.956
I've just got to go
and make a phone call,

618
01:08:48.331 --> 01:08:51.918
and then we'll have
a nice hot cup of tea, huh?

619
01:09:09.936 --> 01:09:13.023
Get me Ziggy, and hurry it up, will you?

620
01:09:13.440 --> 01:09:15.776
It's May Swaisey.

621
01:09:23.116 --> 01:09:25.410
Sprog? Oh, no.

622
01:09:35.545 --> 01:09:36.755
Sprog?

623
01:09:40.342 --> 01:09:41.718
Sprog!

624
01:09:46.223 --> 01:09:47.724
Sprog!

625
01:09:55.774 --> 01:09:57.234
Sprog!

626
01:10:05.158 --> 01:10:06.701
Sprog!

627
01:10:10.997 --> 01:10:12.791
Well, well.

628
01:10:13.416 --> 01:10:15.544
It's our little mother.

629
01:10:19.548 --> 01:10:21.842
That there is Cundalini,

630
01:10:22.384 --> 01:10:25.137
and Cundalini wants his hand back.

631
01:10:27.139 --> 01:10:29.182
I... I want my baby.

632
01:10:29.516 --> 01:10:31.351
Tell you what

633
01:10:32.102 --> 01:10:33.145
I'll swap you.

634
01:10:34.896 --> 01:10:38.316
- Please, give me my baby.
- Jessie.

635
01:10:39.442 --> 01:10:41.778
Jessie, Jessie.

636
01:10:42.362 --> 01:10:44.865
You've not got a sense of humor.

637
01:10:46.032 --> 01:10:49.536
You've got a pretty face, though,
awful pretty.

638
01:10:50.245 --> 01:10:52.706
Yeah, awful pretty.

639
01:10:53.165 --> 01:10:56.918
I suppose you don't need
a sense of humor with a pretty face.

640
01:10:58.044 --> 01:11:00.505
The only trouble is though, missy

641
01:11:00.672 --> 01:11:01.965
if you should

642
01:11:03.550 --> 01:11:04.801
lose the face...

643
01:11:05.010 --> 01:11:06.678
Please, don't hurt my baby.

644
01:11:06.845 --> 01:11:09.806
- ...you've got nothing!
- What do you want from me?

645
01:11:11.183 --> 01:11:14.019
- Don't change the subject.
- Hold it!

646
01:11:15.103 --> 01:11:17.856
- Right there!
- Aah!

647
01:11:18.023 --> 01:11:20.400
- I hate guns.
- Old lady.

648
01:11:20.984 --> 01:11:22.319
Stand back!

649
01:11:22.485 --> 01:11:24.279
- Stay back!
- Woman!

650
01:11:24.821 --> 01:11:26.573
Stay back!

651
01:11:33.997 --> 01:11:36.791
Anyone so much as breathes

652
01:11:36.958 --> 01:11:38.668
I'll cream them!

653
01:11:38.835 --> 01:11:41.129
Open that door.

654
01:11:41.504 --> 01:11:43.590
You get over there.

655
01:11:44.507 --> 01:11:47.302
Put the baby on the ground.

656
01:11:49.679 --> 01:11:51.306
Jessie!

657
01:11:51.473 --> 01:11:52.766
Get the van.

658
01:12:30.845 --> 01:12:34.349
- Gate!
- Don't stop. Just go right through.

659
01:12:58.540 --> 01:12:59.582
Now what?!

660
01:13:06.923 --> 01:13:09.259
- The motor!
- What are you trying to say?

661
01:13:09.426 --> 01:13:11.136
I don't know, it just died on me.

662
01:13:13.305 --> 01:13:15.598
No! Run!

663
01:13:38.580 --> 01:13:40.248
Oh.

664
01:14:02.645 --> 01:14:05.482
No, Jessie!

665
01:14:06.816 --> 01:14:08.735
Lord have mercy!

666
01:14:09.611 --> 01:14:12.030
Lord have mercy!

667
01:14:54.489 --> 01:14:55.698
What do you think?

668
01:14:55.865 --> 01:14:57.909
I'm a doctor, not a fortuneteller.

669
01:14:58.535 --> 01:14:59.661
This your subdural?

670
01:14:59.828 --> 01:15:02.163
- Yes, that's her.
- Lot of problems, huh?

671
01:15:02.330 --> 01:15:05.792
Multiple traumas, spleen,
liver, lung, flail chest

672
01:15:05.959 --> 01:15:08.670
left neck of femur, renal shutdown.

673
01:15:09.045 --> 01:15:11.256
Reads like a grocery list.
She salvageable?

674
01:15:11.423 --> 01:15:14.300
Yeah, sure, we got
all her signs back last night.

675
01:15:14.467 --> 01:15:16.219
- Relatives?
- The husband.

676
01:15:16.386 --> 01:15:18.388
They lost the kid. DOA.

677
01:15:18.972 --> 01:15:23.017
Listen, tell him she's going to
be all right. Tell him not to worry.

678
01:15:23.852 --> 01:15:25.603
If he wants, I'll talk to him.

679
01:15:25.770 --> 01:15:28.356
I don't think he wants to talk to anyone.

680
01:15:29.399 --> 01:15:32.193
He's been standing there
like a zombie all day.

681
01:16:34.631 --> 01:16:36.925
Bubba Zanetti, is that you?

682
01:16:37.634 --> 01:16:39.594
You come for the scooter?

683
01:16:40.261 --> 01:16:42.555
She won't be ready until this afternoon.

684
01:16:42.722 --> 01:16:45.141
Still having trouble with the front forks.

685
01:16:45.308 --> 01:16:47.644
They're mothers to work with.

686
01:16:48.686 --> 01:16:50.146
Hey!

687
01:16:50.355 --> 01:16:53.232
You asshole! What the molly frock
do you think you're doing?

688
01:16:53.316 --> 01:16:56.945
You and me are gonna talk
about the Toecutter.

689
01:16:57.445 --> 01:16:59.781
Never heard of him. Aah!

690
01:16:59.948 --> 01:17:01.658
What the Christ?

691
01:17:01.866 --> 01:17:03.785
I want to know about the Toecutter.

692
01:17:03.952 --> 01:17:05.703
I mind my own business, don't I?

693
01:17:05.870 --> 01:17:07.872
I mean, they'd kill me if I didn't.

694
01:17:22.845 --> 01:17:26.599
I'll say the names and
you say "yes" or "no."

695
01:17:28.017 --> 01:17:29.894
- Nightrider.
- Yeah.

696
01:17:30.061 --> 01:17:32.230
- The Toecutter.
- Yeah.

697
01:17:32.397 --> 01:17:34.190
- Bubba Zanetti.
- Yes!

698
01:17:34.357 --> 01:17:35.441
There's more?

699
01:17:35.608 --> 01:17:37.527
- They took Johnny.
- Johnny the Boy?

700
01:17:37.694 --> 01:17:39.988
- Yeah. Some others.
- Where?

701
01:17:41.322 --> 01:17:43.408
Out at the beaches, looking for fuel.

702
01:17:43.575 --> 01:17:44.993
Are they coming back?

703
01:17:45.159 --> 01:17:46.995
I don't know.

704
01:17:47.537 --> 01:17:49.080
They got their bikes.

705
01:17:50.081 --> 01:17:52.083
I don't know anymore.

706
01:22:15.054 --> 01:22:17.306
<i>Locate black Pursuit Special.</i>

707
01:22:17.473 --> 01:22:20.184
<i>Unauthorized use by a Main Force officer.</i>

708
01:23:16.198 --> 01:23:18.200
Quit toying, Bubba.

709
01:23:18.367 --> 01:23:21.287
Easy. I know what I'm doing.

710
01:27:45.634 --> 01:27:46.677
Hi.

711
01:27:47.553 --> 01:27:49.346
Hey, man. This...

712
01:27:49.555 --> 01:27:51.515
This isn't what it looks, man.

713
01:27:51.682 --> 01:27:55.477
You know, I... I just came down here
to check it out, and

714
01:27:55.686 --> 01:27:58.022
this guy has already been snuffed.

715
01:27:58.230 --> 01:28:00.274
Nothing you could do for him.

716
01:28:01.775 --> 01:28:03.277
Ankle.

717
01:28:04.778 --> 01:28:06.113
It's okay.

718
01:28:10.409 --> 01:28:12.411
What are you doing, man?

719
01:28:20.294 --> 01:28:22.004
Careful, my ankle! My foot, man!

720
01:28:22.671 --> 01:28:26.383
Hey, listen, I had nothing to do
with anything going on back there, man.

721
01:28:27.551 --> 01:28:30.429
Hey, listen, man, will you?
Listen to me!

722
01:28:30.638 --> 01:28:34.057
Will you listen to me? They were
a hell of a crazy people back there, man.

723
01:28:34.141 --> 01:28:38.437
Some kind of bad people.
I'm not responsible for anything.

724
01:28:40.648 --> 01:28:42.107
Ow. What are you doing?

725
01:28:42.274 --> 01:28:43.901
What are you doing, man?

726
01:28:46.237 --> 01:28:49.073
What do you say?
What are you doing?

727
01:28:49.949 --> 01:28:52.952
Hey, listen, I'm not a bad man.

728
01:28:53.118 --> 01:28:55.621
I'm sick, see? Sick.

729
01:28:56.455 --> 01:28:58.082
What do you call it?

730
01:28:58.249 --> 01:29:00.918
Psychopathic, you know.
Personality disorder.

731
01:29:01.126 --> 01:29:03.462
The judge, man, he said so.

732
01:29:04.129 --> 01:29:05.829
You're not gonna hurt me, are you?

733
01:29:09.009 --> 01:29:12.221
Jesus! You can't kill me!

734
01:29:12.388 --> 01:29:14.598
Not for stealing a man's boots!

735
01:29:16.183 --> 01:29:18.978
He was dead, for Christ sakes!

736
01:29:20.479 --> 01:29:22.731
He won't need them anymore!

737
01:29:24.066 --> 01:29:25.985
What are you doing?

738
01:29:27.194 --> 01:29:30.322
I wanna know what you're doing.

739
01:29:36.036 --> 01:29:39.665
The chain in those handcuffs
is high-tensile steel.

740
01:29:41.292 --> 01:29:44.420
It'd take you 10 minutes
to hack through it with this.

741
01:29:47.047 --> 01:29:49.341
Now, if you're lucky

742
01:29:49.550 --> 01:29:52.761
you could hack through your ankle
in five minutes.

743
01:29:55.180 --> 01:29:57.099
You're mad, man!

744
01:29:57.474 --> 01:30:00.185
You think I look silly, don't you?

745
01:30:01.937 --> 01:30:03.981
Don't bring this on me, man.

746
01:30:04.148 --> 01:30:05.941
Don't do this to me!

747
01:30:06.108 --> 01:30:09.153
Please, sweet Jesus. I was sick!

748
01:30:09.320 --> 01:30:11.947
Don't bring this on me, please!

